![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ac4c809c-3bfe-4291-a87f-fa1e14c2b8a5/20240415_022211.jpg?format=original)

Rossy Ogawa, the founder of the Marigold Women's Pro Wrestling promotion, recently shared intriguing comments regarding the possibility of a partnership between Marigold and WWE.

Speaking about Marigold's potential relationship with WWE, Ogawa remarked, "Maybe it will become a (WWE) ranch.'' This cryptic statement hints at the prospect of a collaborative endeavor between the two wrestling entities.

Ogawa further elaborated on his sentiments, expressing gratitude towards WWE for their support. He stated, "(WWE) has been very good to me. I think they're buying into what I've been doing to raise Iyo, Kairi, and Julia."

This acknowledgment of WWE's recognition of Marigold's talent underscores the growing synergy between the two organizations.

Rossy Ogawa and Giulia were in town during WrestleMania weekend, fueling speculation about a potential working relationship between WWE and Marigold. This visit suggests that discussions are underway to explore collaboration opportunities between the two wrestling promotions.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/f193ef08-388d-4c7b-b4f8-5a57190c10f1/giulia-1.jpg?format=original)

One of the key aspects of this potential partnership revolves around Giulia, a prominent wrestler associated with both Marigold and WWE.

While it's believed that Giulia's time will be divided between NXT and Marigold, there have been previous reports from Fightful indicating her expected WWE in-ring debut at NXT Heatwave.

However, according to the Wrestling Observer, the uncertainty surrounding Giulia's visa arrangements and potential obstacles could impact the timeline of her debut.

The prospect of a partnership between WWE and Marigold presents exciting opportunities for both parties. For Marigold, it signifies an opportunity to expand its reach and exposure on a global scale, leveraging WWE's vast platform and resources.

Meanwhile, for WWE, collaboration with Marigold could provide access to a pool of talented wrestlers and unique storytelling opportunities in the burgeoning women's wrestling scene.

While details regarding the extent and nature of this potential collaboration remain undisclosed, Ogawa's comments hint at an optimistic outlook for the future.

He suggested that there may be "some kind of announcement from the other side in the future," indicating that developments regarding the partnership may be forthcoming.